latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Such a heart touching and relatable video this is! Working from home has been challenging but I feel proud  of all things we achieved last year. Let's all take a pause, pat our back and feel proud of ourselves, coz "Women make it happen"! 
Cheers!

latestIgtvVideos.title: COCOA ENERGY BALLS
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
|COCOA ENERGY BALLS| • |Episode12|
#SavourySaturdaysWithYuvika - #KidsSpecial .

I can bet, your kid is gonna drool over this easiest and the most amazing recipe ever. It literally just took me a couple of minutes to combine all of these together and has the most basic ingredients . .
Here's the list: -Cocoa powder
-Roasted sesame seeds
-Raisins
-Almonds
.
.

Process:
- Roast the sesame seeds lightly so as to eliminate their raw flavour.
- After they completely cool down, grind it along with the other ingredients together in the grinder. - Once done, make balls of it.
- If you want, you can dip or just drizzle some Hershey's chocolate sauce over it. I do it because Dhiyara just absolutely loves it🥳 .
.
You can store them for over a week. Isn't it just amazing! And all you mama's having sugar cravings but can't have because of diet, I got yaa! 👯🏻‍♀
.
.
Go ahead, make this supremely easy, healthy cocoa energy balls and do not forget to tell me, how do you and your kid find it? .

latestIgtvVideos.title: MOONG DAL CHILLA
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Episode11 #SavourySaturdaysWithYuvika - #KidsSpecial
.
Since, I am sharing kids special recipes with ya'll, I thought why not bring in my special kid in the video today for some fun. •MOONG DAL CHILLA • 
This is probably the recipe which we moms got from our moms and we just can't seem to get over this amazing protein packed meal. .
Dhiyara absolutely loves this but with cheese, ofcourse.  But to make it extra nutritious and filling I like to add in some veggies. Whatever is available with you, just go ahead with it in hearty amount! .

Ingredients:
-1 cup Moong Dal
-Peas- ground to a paste
-Salt to taste
-1 tablespoon ghee or butter
.

Procedure:
-soak the moong dal overnight.
-Grind it to a fine paste, add all the ingredients. -Make cheelas after the pan is heated and we'll greased up with some ghee/butter
-Grate some cheese and put in some sliced mushrooms, coriander leaves and other vegetables. -Ta-Daaa!!🤟🏻 Enjoy this delicious recipe and let your kids receive the benefits of it while loving it too. No nakhras, I swear💜. I hope you all enjoyed watching Dhiyara for the first time ever on Savoury Saturdays. And let me know, if you want more of her! 
Also, do not forget to tag me when you make them using the hashtag #SavourySaturdaysWithYuvika 
I'd love to see your version of it.💜 .
